'''Tivydale, Texas''' is an [[unincorporated area|unincorporated farming and ranching community]] located in [[Gillespie County, Texas|Gillespie County]], fourteen miles west of [[Fredericksburg, Texas|Fredericksburg]], and was originally known as Bunkesville and Pumpkinville.

==Establishment==

Tivydale is named for Joseph Albert Tivy. Born in [[Canada]] and later a former [[Texas Ranger Division|Texas Ranger]], Tivy was an adventurer and entrepreneur.  He had joined the [[California Gold Rush]], fought in the [[Civil War (United States)|Civil War]], served in legislatures both in [[California]] and in [[Texas]], and later became mayor of [[Kerrville, Texas|Kerrville]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Captain Joseph A. Tivy|url=http://www.9key.com/markers/marker_detail.asp?atlas_number=5265000724|work=Texas Historical Markers|publisher=William Nienke, Sam Morrow|accessdate=13 January 2011}}</ref>

Tivy had bought several thousand acres of land in 1847 and 1848.<ref>Texas General Land Office title searches</ref> Between 1877 and 1885, he sold land in the Pedernales River valley. Tivy died in 1892 and is buried at the Y.O. Ranch in [[Mountain Home, Texas|Mountain Home]].<ref>{{Find a Grave|7809734|Captain Joseph Albert Tivy}}</ref>

The German-music Bunkesville Band was a popular area entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kohout|first=Martin Donell|title=Tivydale, Texas|url=http://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/hrt25|work=Handbook of Texas Online|publisher=Texas State Historical Association|accessdate=13 January 2011}}</ref>

==Sch<U+00FC>tzenfest==

Tivydale has an active sch<U+00FC>tzenbund (shooting club) and participates in the annual Gillespie County Bundes Sch<U+00FC>tzenfest.  The event includes crowning of one or more Sch<U+00FC>tzenk<U+00F6>nigs (shooting kings), a parade and a [[Saengerfest]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Sch<U+00FC>tzenfest Returns For 115th Year July 31, 2010|url=http://www.fredericksburgstandard.com/articles/2010/07/22/events/02event.txt|accessdate=31 January 2011|newspaper=Fredericksburg Standard|date=21 July 2010}}</ref>

